The paper discusses a non-orthogonal multiple access technology for future communications, which falls under the category of communication and information theory (cs.IT). The proposed receiver is designed to reduce the complexity of message passing algorithm (MPA), which is commonly used in SCMA systems. Therefore, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of communication and networking (cs.COMM), network infrastructure (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), and machine learning (cs.LG) as these areas are closely related to the design and optimization of communication systems.
